I got sopes con chorizo, my partner got la chancla con veggies, both of us got tamales and guacamole and chips. My sopes were hearty and the meat was not too greasy, as can happen at other places with chorizo. The tamales were moist, and the homemade chips and guacamole were banging. Only reason for four instead of five stars, my partner said her chancla lacked just a little more flavor, which just means they probably didn’t over salt it. :) There were leftovers of all of it, too. Definitely a local place for locals but if you’re in town, go!
